1
00:00:11,710 --> 00:00:18,380
[2010]

2
00:00:20,760 --> 00:00:21,440
Cold, huh?

3
00:00:33,560 --> 00:00:34,240
Cheng.

4
00:00:35,710 --> 00:00:37,390
Can you please not go?

5
00:00:39,790 --> 00:00:41,640
I can't always be by your side.

6
00:00:43,070 --> 00:00:44,470
You have to be a good girl.

7
00:00:45,310 --> 00:00:46,570
If anyone bullies you,

8
00:00:47,110 --> 00:00:48,370
just go to Jiang Cheng.

9
00:00:55,440 --> 00:00:56,390
You're a man now,

10
00:00:56,920 --> 00:00:58,850
so look after our sister properly.

11
00:01:00,520 --> 00:01:01,200
Cheng,

12
00:01:02,000 --> 00:01:03,000
come back soon.

13
00:01:16,340 --> 00:01:17,140
Be a good girl.

14
00:02:07,320 --> 00:02:08,000
Jin,

15
00:02:08,940 --> 00:02:10,919
just cry if you want to.

16
00:02:15,050 --> 00:02:15,920
I won't cry.

17
00:02:37,030 --> 00:02:37,710
I'm home.

18
00:02:51,800 --> 00:02:52,530
Jiang Cheng?

19
00:02:54,590 --> 00:02:55,320
Jiang Cheng!

20
00:03:09,430 --> 00:03:10,100
Zhou Jin.

21
00:03:13,120 --> 00:03:13,940
Hansheng.

22
00:04:46,409 --> 00:04:52,030
[Sunsets Secrets Regrets]

23
00:04:52,400 --> 00:04:54,730
[Episode 19]

24
00:05:25,220 --> 00:05:25,950
Officer,

25
00:05:26,430 --> 00:05:27,400
take my shoes off

26
00:05:27,740 --> 00:05:29,000
so I can loosen up a bit.

27
00:05:31,240 --> 00:05:33,170
I'm talking to you—did you hear me?

28
00:05:34,100 --> 00:05:35,659
Boss, Boss,

29
00:05:35,870 --> 00:05:37,020
well, something happened in his family.

30
00:05:37,020 --> 00:05:37,780
Just look at him.

31
00:05:37,780 --> 00:05:39,810
If there's anything you need, I'll do it!

32
00:05:39,810 --> 00:05:40,659
Get lost!

33
00:05:44,580 --> 00:05:45,780
Are you deaf today or what?

34
00:05:45,780 --> 00:05:47,380
Did your dad die, or your mom?

35
00:05:48,100 --> 00:05:48,960
Or did your girl

36
00:05:49,260 --> 00:05:50,790
get screwed by another guy?

37
00:05:53,830 --> 00:05:54,690
Say that again.

38
00:05:55,100 --> 00:05:56,040
I asked—

39
00:05:56,460 --> 00:05:57,550
did your dad die, or your mom?

40
00:05:57,550 --> 00:05:59,950
Or did your girl
get screwed by another guy?

41
00:06:08,220 --> 00:06:09,330
What happened after?

42
00:06:09,330 --> 00:06:11,240
It all died down after that.

43
00:06:11,900 --> 00:06:13,340
Criminals are human too.

44
00:06:13,360 --> 00:06:15,050
And humans fear death.

45
00:06:13,720 --> 00:06:15,110
[Dan]

46
00:06:17,830 --> 00:06:18,870
I'm going to take a call.

47
00:06:18,870 --> 00:06:19,260
Okay.

48
00:06:21,220 --> 00:06:22,630
Dan, what happened?

49
00:06:23,140 --> 00:06:24,740
Zhou Jin, come back quickly.

50
00:06:25,070 --> 00:06:25,950
What's wrong?

51
00:06:26,260 --> 00:06:27,510
Something's off with Jiang Cheng,

52
00:06:27,510 --> 00:06:28,700
and he won't say anything.

53
00:06:28,700 --> 00:06:30,030
You'd better come back.

54
00:06:31,430 --> 00:06:32,560
Does Chief Tan know?

55
00:06:33,220 --> 00:06:35,430
He's the one who asked me to call you.

56
00:06:35,850 --> 00:06:37,700
He wants you to question Jiang Cheng.

57
00:06:37,700 --> 00:06:39,750
He wouldn't say anything
about Old Scorpion

58
00:06:39,750 --> 00:06:41,700
or Leader Yao.

59
00:06:41,830 --> 00:06:43,830
He just kept asking if you were here.

60
00:06:43,830 --> 00:06:45,159
When will you come back?

61
00:06:46,950 --> 00:06:48,350
Okay, I'll be right back.

62
00:06:53,220 --> 00:06:53,630
Sirs.

63
00:06:55,580 --> 00:06:56,310
You're here.

64
00:07:00,390 --> 00:07:01,250
I remember you.

65
00:07:02,020 --> 00:07:03,280
On Zhao Xiaoyu's case.

66
00:07:03,950 --> 00:07:05,210
Hello, Commander Liu.

67
00:07:11,760 --> 00:07:14,090
Commander Liu, maybe just let her try?

68
00:07:14,870 --> 00:07:16,830
Investigations require efficiency.

69
00:07:16,830 --> 00:07:18,760
We can't let this standoff drag on.

70
00:07:22,900 --> 00:07:24,430
Let's see how it goes first.

71
00:07:27,580 --> 00:07:28,260
Zhou Jin!

72
00:07:29,310 --> 00:07:30,310
Zhou Jin!

73
00:07:30,330 --> 00:07:31,590
Stop yelling! Shut up!

74
00:07:32,950 --> 00:07:34,260
Alright, calm down.

75
00:07:34,580 --> 00:07:35,310
Jiang Cheng,

76
00:07:35,580 --> 00:07:37,430
what's in your best interest right now

77
00:07:37,430 --> 00:07:38,900
is to clearly explain what happened

78
00:07:38,900 --> 00:07:40,560
after the Jingang Wharf deal.

79
00:07:40,700 --> 00:07:42,460
Otherwise, the longer it drags on,

80
00:07:42,460 --> 00:07:44,120
the more suspicious we'll be.

81
00:07:45,220 --> 00:07:46,550
What do you mean by that?

82
00:07:48,630 --> 00:07:49,700
Haven't we always been

83
00:07:49,700 --> 00:07:50,960
talking to you nicely?

84
00:07:51,630 --> 00:07:52,990
Destroying the drug factory—

85
00:07:52,990 --> 00:07:54,720
yes, you do get credit for that.

86
00:07:55,310 --> 00:07:56,630
But please think about it:

87
00:07:56,630 --> 00:07:58,750
now the main culprits
are either dead or have fled.

88
00:07:58,750 --> 00:08:00,280
There's a lot we don't know,

89
00:08:00,340 --> 00:08:02,740
and you've never given us
a straight answer

90
00:08:03,310 --> 00:08:04,770
about how Leader Yao died.

91
00:08:05,450 --> 00:08:06,360
You said you're Cangfeng.

92
00:08:06,360 --> 00:08:07,750
Fine, we all believe you.

93
00:08:07,750 --> 00:08:09,750
But before everything
is investigated clearly,

94
00:08:09,750 --> 00:08:11,080
you're still suspected

95
00:08:11,140 --> 00:08:13,950
of involvement in
organized crime and intentional homicide.

96
00:08:13,950 --> 00:08:15,150
You can't avoid that.

97
00:08:15,900 --> 00:08:16,660
I told you,

98
00:08:16,900 --> 00:08:18,230
get Zhou Jin here for me.

99
00:08:26,870 --> 00:08:27,730
Commander Liu,

100
00:08:27,870 --> 00:08:29,390
although we can't fully prove

101
00:08:29,390 --> 00:08:30,950
that Jiang Cheng is innocent right now,

102
00:08:30,950 --> 00:08:32,880
if he really had something to hide,

103
00:08:33,070 --> 00:08:35,400
why would he have
passed information to us?

104
00:08:35,400 --> 00:08:36,340
Can I go in and talk

105
00:08:36,340 --> 00:08:36,909
to him?

106
00:08:37,990 --> 00:08:39,990
Why did he specifically ask for you?

107
00:08:42,679 --> 00:08:43,280
What

108
00:08:44,420 --> 00:08:46,150
exactly is your relationship?

109
00:08:48,160 --> 00:08:49,830
We were almost married.

110
00:08:55,080 --> 00:08:56,080
Professor Jiang.

111
00:09:00,790 --> 00:09:01,650
Commander Liu.

112
00:09:18,100 --> 00:09:18,960
Commander Liu,

113
00:09:19,030 --> 00:09:20,560
I wasn't finished just now.

114
00:09:21,200 --> 00:09:22,170
I promise

115
00:09:22,960 --> 00:09:24,110
I won't let my personal relationship

116
00:09:24,110 --> 00:09:26,070
with him affect my professional judgment.

117
00:09:26,070 --> 00:09:27,030
I know exactly

118
00:09:27,070 --> 00:09:28,160
what to ask

119
00:09:28,300 --> 00:09:29,900
and what to get him to answer.

120
00:09:30,050 --> 00:09:31,220
Right now, we're just stuck here.

121
00:09:31,220 --> 00:09:32,680
Why not let me go in and try?

122
00:09:32,770 --> 00:09:34,400
If it really doesn't work out,
I'll come back out.

123
00:09:34,400 --> 00:09:35,130
Is that okay?

124
00:09:35,190 --> 00:09:36,320
Yes, Commander Liu.

125
00:09:36,700 --> 00:09:37,970
Getting him to calm down

126
00:09:37,970 --> 00:09:38,690
and open up

127
00:09:38,850 --> 00:09:39,780
is the priority.

128
00:09:46,450 --> 00:09:47,650
Alright, I agree.

129
00:09:48,730 --> 00:09:49,480
Then...

130
00:09:49,760 --> 00:09:50,820
let's give it a try.

131
00:09:52,900 --> 00:09:53,760
Commander Liu,

132
00:09:54,460 --> 00:09:55,860
I'd like to speak with you

133
00:09:56,180 --> 00:09:57,110
about this case.

134
00:09:59,860 --> 00:10:00,460
Chief Tan.

135
00:10:01,920 --> 00:10:02,850
Let's pause for a moment.

136
00:10:02,850 --> 00:10:03,380
Yes.

137
00:10:15,730 --> 00:10:16,760
What's going on?

138
00:10:17,590 --> 00:10:18,800
What do you mean, what's going on?

139
00:10:18,800 --> 00:10:21,400
What's going on
between you and the guy inside?

140
00:10:22,030 --> 00:10:23,360
That was a long time ago.

141
00:10:25,350 --> 00:10:26,830
Then explain it clearly.

142
00:10:26,980 --> 00:10:29,840
What if your significant other
gets the wrong idea?

143
00:10:31,120 --> 00:10:33,050
I'll step out and take a look first.

144
00:11:18,310 --> 00:11:19,240
Why are you here?

145
00:11:20,240 --> 00:11:22,100
Just came to check on things here.

146
00:11:22,910 --> 00:11:24,640
What did you say to the leaders?

147
00:11:26,870 --> 00:11:27,400
Zhou Jin.

148
00:11:27,610 --> 00:11:28,110
Professor Jiang.

149
00:11:28,110 --> 00:11:29,110
Professor Jiang!

150
00:11:29,180 --> 00:11:30,230
The leaders have instructed us

151
00:11:30,230 --> 00:11:31,510
to fully cooperate with you

152
00:11:31,510 --> 00:11:33,110
and Professor Jiang's work.

153
00:11:33,930 --> 00:11:35,460
Although Jiang Cheng is
still under suspicion,

154
00:11:35,460 --> 00:11:37,630
questioning him in an interrogation room
isn't suitable.

155
00:11:37,630 --> 00:11:39,850
Undercovers have to maintain vigilance
for extended periods,

156
00:11:39,850 --> 00:11:42,610
making them highly sensitive
to changes in their environment.

157
00:11:42,610 --> 00:11:43,880
He must've been sleep-deprived
for a long time,

158
00:11:43,880 --> 00:11:45,520
which makes him sensitive to light.

159
00:11:45,520 --> 00:11:46,630
The lights in the interrogation room

160
00:11:46,630 --> 00:11:48,360
will only agitate him further.

161
00:11:48,990 --> 00:11:50,780
I've already suggested to the leaders

162
00:11:50,780 --> 00:11:51,250
that we move him

163
00:11:51,250 --> 00:11:53,110
to a less stressful environment.

164
00:11:53,350 --> 00:11:53,820
Also,

165
00:11:54,350 --> 00:11:56,480
turn off the surveillance equipment.

166
00:11:57,830 --> 00:11:58,280
Okay.

167
00:11:58,660 --> 00:11:59,990
Let us prepare for this.

168
00:12:00,150 --> 00:12:00,680
Let's go.

169
00:12:07,300 --> 00:12:07,870
Zhou Jin,

170
00:12:08,300 --> 00:12:09,700
you have only half an hour

171
00:12:09,790 --> 00:12:10,920
to question him.

172
00:12:26,060 --> 00:12:28,120
I know you've been worried about him.

173
00:12:28,780 --> 00:12:29,540
Don't rush.

174
00:12:30,870 --> 00:12:32,070
I'll be there for you.

175
00:13:07,110 --> 00:13:07,840
Jiang Cheng,

176
00:13:08,070 --> 00:13:09,600
we brought Zhou Jin for you.

177
00:13:09,960 --> 00:13:11,290
I hope you can stay calm.

178
00:13:23,440 --> 00:13:23,970
Alright.

179
00:13:26,270 --> 00:13:26,990
Jiang Cheng,

180
00:13:26,990 --> 00:13:29,450
everything you know
is very important to us.

181
00:13:30,040 --> 00:13:31,680
Laying out the situation clearly

182
00:13:31,680 --> 00:13:32,960
will help both you

183
00:13:33,300 --> 00:13:34,030
and the case.

184
00:13:47,870 --> 00:13:48,540
Jin.

185
00:13:58,400 --> 00:13:59,400
Jiang Hansheng.

186
00:13:59,770 --> 00:14:01,430
I mentioned him to you before.

187
00:14:02,750 --> 00:14:03,950
It's been a long time,

188
00:14:04,060 --> 00:14:04,880
Jiang Cheng.

189
00:14:08,620 --> 00:14:09,910
It's been a long time.

190
00:14:11,210 --> 00:14:12,250
You two have met?

191
00:14:12,280 --> 00:14:13,070
Of course.

192
00:14:13,400 --> 00:14:15,200
The young master from No. 23.

193
00:14:20,270 --> 00:14:21,150
Are you okay?

194
00:14:21,650 --> 00:14:23,270
Should we call a doctor to check on you?

195
00:14:23,270 --> 00:14:23,820
I'm fine.

196
00:14:35,910 --> 00:14:36,750
Jin,

197
00:14:37,820 --> 00:14:39,150
I've missed you so much.

198
00:14:42,810 --> 00:14:43,740
I need to ask you

199
00:14:44,470 --> 00:14:45,890
a few things.

200
00:14:50,420 --> 00:14:51,820
What do you want to ask me?

201
00:14:52,510 --> 00:14:54,040
Have I ever killed someone?

202
00:14:55,350 --> 00:14:56,270
I said I'm Cangfeng,

203
00:14:56,270 --> 00:14:58,060
and everything I've done
in the past five years

204
00:14:58,060 --> 00:14:59,110
was for the case,

205
00:14:59,700 --> 00:15:00,910
but did any of you believe me?

206
00:15:00,910 --> 00:15:01,940
I believe you.

207
00:15:04,460 --> 00:15:05,990
Jiang Cheng, I believe you.

208
00:15:07,350 --> 00:15:09,080
As long as you tell me the truth,

209
00:15:10,180 --> 00:15:11,080
I will help you.

210
00:15:15,660 --> 00:15:17,190
You've really changed a lot

211
00:15:17,910 --> 00:15:19,110
over the years.

212
00:15:24,270 --> 00:15:25,270
Sit down first.

213
00:15:26,970 --> 00:15:28,700
It wasn't easy to arrange this.

214
00:15:28,710 --> 00:15:30,270
You don't have much time left.

215
00:15:30,270 --> 00:15:31,930
You need to cooperate with me.

216
00:15:33,150 --> 00:15:33,630
Okay.

217
00:15:43,540 --> 00:15:44,470
Are you alright?

218
00:15:48,700 --> 00:15:50,390
Why did you insist on seeing Zhou Jin?

219
00:15:50,390 --> 00:15:51,450
Because I like her.

220
00:15:52,850 --> 00:15:54,010
Quit joking around.

221
00:15:54,250 --> 00:15:55,040
I'm not.

222
00:15:55,060 --> 00:15:56,520
Everything I said is true.

223
00:15:58,130 --> 00:15:59,730
Did Jin not tell you

224
00:16:00,330 --> 00:16:01,420
that we were together for seven years

225
00:16:01,420 --> 00:16:02,700
and even got engaged?

226
00:16:04,080 --> 00:16:05,270
The past is the past.

227
00:16:05,720 --> 00:16:06,650
You have a point.

228
00:16:07,320 --> 00:16:09,380
But some things can never be changed.

229
00:16:09,790 --> 00:16:12,090
Jin and I have had
so many misunderstandings.

230
00:16:12,090 --> 00:16:13,620
Now that we've finally met,

231
00:16:13,660 --> 00:16:14,390
there's so much

232
00:16:14,390 --> 00:16:16,350
I want to catch up on with her,
just the two of us.

233
00:16:16,350 --> 00:16:17,110
I think

234
00:16:17,830 --> 00:16:20,360
you can understand, right,
Professor Jiang?

235
00:16:21,730 --> 00:16:22,460
Jiang Cheng,

236
00:16:23,470 --> 00:16:25,380
this meeting today, in this environment,

237
00:16:25,380 --> 00:16:26,650
was arranged

238
00:16:26,890 --> 00:16:29,350
with my personal reputation
as a guarantee.

239
00:16:29,640 --> 00:16:30,470
We don't need

240
00:16:30,470 --> 00:16:32,730
to waste time on meaningless arguments.

241
00:16:33,860 --> 00:16:34,430
Also,

242
00:16:36,390 --> 00:16:38,120
it has already been turned off.

243
00:16:45,470 --> 00:16:46,930
I'll ask you one last time:

244
00:16:47,520 --> 00:16:49,580
why did you insist on seeing Zhou Jin?

245
00:16:53,370 --> 00:16:54,250
Who is the mole?

246
00:16:54,820 --> 00:16:56,550
He's the one who got Yao killed.

247
00:16:56,560 --> 00:16:57,130
Tell me!

248
00:17:02,420 --> 00:17:03,450
I can't tell you.

249
00:17:05,740 --> 00:17:07,339
Once we find out everything,

250
00:17:07,460 --> 00:17:09,260
he'll definitely pay the price.

251
00:17:09,950 --> 00:17:10,390
Tell me,

252
00:17:10,390 --> 00:17:12,050
how do you know there is a mole?

253
00:17:20,339 --> 00:17:21,339
How's your wound?

254
00:17:23,060 --> 00:17:23,740
I'm fine.

255
00:17:25,670 --> 00:17:27,670
When we were investigating Lai San,

256
00:17:27,670 --> 00:17:29,260
when Yao returned to your precinct,

257
00:17:29,260 --> 00:17:30,860
and even before you found me—

258
00:17:31,300 --> 00:17:34,580
this mole had been leaking the progress
of the police investigation.

259
00:17:34,580 --> 00:17:36,230
On the day of the Jingang Wharf deal,

260
00:17:36,230 --> 00:17:37,870
they took out Yao's photo

261
00:17:37,950 --> 00:17:39,580
and said he would definitely come.

262
00:17:39,580 --> 00:17:42,180
That's when I became
even more certain of this.

263
00:17:43,340 --> 00:17:44,530
After you escaped,

264
00:17:44,780 --> 00:17:46,110
what exactly did you do?

265
00:17:47,340 --> 00:17:49,060
How did Leader Yao

266
00:17:49,780 --> 00:17:50,980
and Meng Junfeng die?

267
00:17:54,190 --> 00:17:54,740
I...

268
00:18:01,740 --> 00:18:02,910
Under those circumstances,

269
00:18:02,910 --> 00:18:04,640
I really couldn't do anything.

270
00:18:05,780 --> 00:18:07,500
I could only watch as Old Scorpion

271
00:18:07,500 --> 00:18:08,580
killed them.

272
00:18:18,870 --> 00:18:19,470
Jin,

273
00:18:20,060 --> 00:18:21,020
there's something more important

274
00:18:21,020 --> 00:18:22,020
I need to tell you.

275
00:18:26,850 --> 00:18:27,230
For the past few years,

276
00:18:27,230 --> 00:18:29,100
I've been working for He Wu.

277
00:18:29,670 --> 00:18:30,990
You already know about his company,

278
00:18:30,990 --> 00:18:32,120
Hengyun Logistics.

279
00:18:32,260 --> 00:18:34,460
Besides transporting ordinary goods,

280
00:18:34,710 --> 00:18:37,110
they've also smuggled drugs and gun parts.

281
00:18:37,390 --> 00:18:39,250
I gave Yao a few USB drives before.

282
00:18:39,390 --> 00:18:40,260
Those drives contain

283
00:18:40,260 --> 00:18:41,500
videos of their deals

284
00:18:41,740 --> 00:18:44,150
and records
of their financial transactions.

285
00:18:44,150 --> 00:18:45,800
Yao kept all those USB drives

286
00:18:45,830 --> 00:18:47,540
in a safe-deposit box at Guangqi Bank.

287
00:18:47,540 --> 00:18:48,540
Whenever we got new evidence,

288
00:18:48,540 --> 00:18:49,670
he'd put it there.

289
00:18:50,060 --> 00:18:51,780
Originally, we planned to
settle everything

290
00:18:51,780 --> 00:18:53,300
once the operation concluded.

291
00:18:53,300 --> 00:18:54,430
Now that He Wu is dead

292
00:18:54,630 --> 00:18:55,500
and Old Scorpion has fled,

293
00:18:55,500 --> 00:18:56,830
many leads will go cold.

294
00:18:57,230 --> 00:18:58,710
As long as you retrieve those USB drives,

295
00:18:58,710 --> 00:19:01,640
you can thoroughly investigate
Hengyun Logistics.

296
00:19:01,920 --> 00:19:03,200
Now that my cover

297
00:19:03,230 --> 00:19:04,260
is blown,

298
00:19:04,260 --> 00:19:06,020
Old Scorpion will definitely make a move.

299
00:19:06,020 --> 00:19:07,260
So you must hurry.

300
00:19:10,540 --> 00:19:12,540
What kind of person is Old Scorpion?

301
00:19:16,260 --> 00:19:18,190
Old Scorpion is the sniper you saw.

302
00:19:23,260 --> 00:19:24,320
He is Old Scorpion?

303
00:19:26,860 --> 00:19:28,120
Qi Yan is Old Scorpion?

304
00:19:30,630 --> 00:19:31,830
I originally thought

305
00:19:32,610 --> 00:19:34,630
Qi Yan was Old Scorpion's subordinate too.

306
00:19:34,630 --> 00:19:35,670
It was only after coming to Jingang Wharf

307
00:19:35,670 --> 00:19:36,870
that I figured it out.

308
00:19:37,670 --> 00:19:39,200
I have to thank Yao for that.

309
00:19:39,670 --> 00:19:41,270
Because Yao recognized him.

310
00:19:41,540 --> 00:19:42,130
However,

311
00:19:42,150 --> 00:19:44,430
I've never heard anyone else
call him Qi Yan.

312
00:19:44,430 --> 00:19:45,670
Those close to him

313
00:19:45,740 --> 00:19:47,200
call him Young Master Wen.

314
00:19:47,500 --> 00:19:49,020
It seems like some kind of honorific

315
00:19:49,020 --> 00:19:50,060
or a nickname.

316
00:19:51,580 --> 00:19:53,150
This person usually
hides behind the scenes,

317
00:19:53,150 --> 00:19:54,430
lurking in the shadows.

318
00:19:54,430 --> 00:19:55,670
He has no public identity—

319
00:19:55,670 --> 00:19:56,670
none of us saw him in person

320
00:19:56,670 --> 00:19:58,730
unless it was absolutely necessary.

321
00:19:58,990 --> 00:19:59,950
He has an old man working under him

322
00:19:59,950 --> 00:20:01,260
who goes by the name Qi,

323
00:20:01,780 --> 00:20:03,640
whose words carry a lot of weight.

324
00:20:04,000 --> 00:20:04,910
For a long time, I'd believed

325
00:20:04,910 --> 00:20:06,060
Qi was Old Scorpion.

326
00:20:07,470 --> 00:20:08,990
He also has a woman under him

327
00:20:08,990 --> 00:20:09,870
named Qiu Ye.

328
00:20:10,060 --> 00:20:11,790
Qi Yan trusts those two deeply.

329
00:20:12,280 --> 00:20:13,190
After the Jingang Wharf deal,

330
00:20:13,190 --> 00:20:14,150
even though you sealed

331
00:20:14,150 --> 00:20:15,690
all the exits and mountain passes,

332
00:20:15,690 --> 00:20:16,550
it was useless.

333
00:20:17,260 --> 00:20:17,990
After abandoning

334
00:20:17,990 --> 00:20:19,250
their expendable men,

335
00:20:19,390 --> 00:20:21,470
their real bases are all underground.

336
00:20:21,470 --> 00:20:24,000
They split up
and moved to several locations.

337
00:20:24,100 --> 00:20:25,390
I was blindfolded the entire time,

338
00:20:25,390 --> 00:20:27,150
unable to tell day from night.

339
00:20:27,500 --> 00:20:29,230
I was just being dragged along.

340
00:20:29,630 --> 00:20:31,300
The Jingang Wharf deal was just a setup.

341
00:20:31,300 --> 00:20:32,710
It was designed to deal with Yao Weihai

342
00:20:32,710 --> 00:20:35,170
and the undercover
he'd planted in the gang.

343
00:20:36,500 --> 00:20:38,540
Old Scorpion no longer needs to
import drugs.

344
00:20:38,540 --> 00:20:40,910
He has mature manufacturing technology

345
00:20:41,060 --> 00:20:42,860
and a complete production line.

346
00:20:48,820 --> 00:20:51,080
Having investigated up to this point...

347
00:20:52,230 --> 00:20:53,760
you could've wrapped it up.

348
00:20:59,390 --> 00:21:00,230
But Yao died.

349
00:21:07,820 --> 00:21:09,780
Fortunately, you were smart enough

350
00:21:09,780 --> 00:21:10,720
to reach me.

351
00:21:11,820 --> 00:21:12,710
Even if I die,

352
00:21:12,710 --> 00:21:14,510
I have to pass on all the evidence

353
00:21:14,820 --> 00:21:15,430
and leads

354
00:21:15,430 --> 00:21:17,230
I've gathered over these years.

355
00:21:17,610 --> 00:21:19,410
Even if it only brings down He Wu,

356
00:21:20,260 --> 00:21:21,430
losing my life

357
00:21:22,260 --> 00:21:23,590
would still be worth it.

358
00:21:26,990 --> 00:21:28,230
They thought blindfolding me

359
00:21:28,230 --> 00:21:30,230
could hide the factory's location.

360
00:21:31,390 --> 00:21:32,540
But you know me.

361
00:21:33,230 --> 00:21:33,950
Remember the nickname

362
00:21:33,950 --> 00:21:35,550
you gave me when we were kids?

363
00:21:36,780 --> 00:21:37,580
Bloodhound.

364
00:21:38,340 --> 00:21:38,740
Yeah.

365
00:21:39,990 --> 00:21:41,650
My nose has always been sharp.

366
00:21:42,300 --> 00:21:44,430
Along the way,
I quietly kept track of the time

367
00:21:44,430 --> 00:21:46,630
and the directions the vehicle turned.

368
00:21:46,870 --> 00:21:48,160
Even if you hadn't come,

369
00:21:48,160 --> 00:21:51,360
I could've figured out
the exact location of the factory.

370
00:21:53,470 --> 00:21:55,160
That's all the intelligence

371
00:21:55,190 --> 00:21:56,520
I can provide right now.

372
00:21:57,340 --> 00:21:58,670
I have only one request—

373
00:21:59,260 --> 00:22:01,150
reinstate my identity
as a police officer ASAP.

374
00:22:01,150 --> 00:22:03,150
I want to catch Old Scorpion myself.

375
00:22:08,630 --> 00:22:09,150
Jin,

376
00:22:09,710 --> 00:22:10,580
believe me.

377
00:22:11,500 --> 00:22:12,430
I have never done anything

378
00:22:12,430 --> 00:22:13,760
that betrayed my faith.

379
00:22:14,740 --> 00:22:16,190
Five years is a long time.

380
00:22:16,780 --> 00:22:17,870
I can grit my teeth

381
00:22:17,900 --> 00:22:18,600
and bear everything

382
00:22:18,600 --> 00:22:20,340
that's happened.

383
00:22:20,360 --> 00:22:21,490
But from now on,

384
00:22:21,910 --> 00:22:24,970
I don't want my own people
talking behind my back again.

385
00:22:27,670 --> 00:22:28,530
I, Jiang Cheng,

386
00:22:29,470 --> 00:22:30,930
have a clear conscience.

387
00:22:36,630 --> 00:22:37,230
Jin.

388
00:22:38,740 --> 00:22:40,200
For the past five years...

389
00:22:42,540 --> 00:22:44,140
I was carrying out a mission.

390
00:22:44,780 --> 00:22:45,670
I had no choice.

391
00:22:59,360 --> 00:23:00,880
Right now, the most important thing

392
00:23:00,880 --> 00:23:02,280
is to find the USB drives.

393
00:23:02,590 --> 00:23:04,110
Once the evidence is secured,

394
00:23:04,110 --> 00:23:05,840
your identity will be obvious.

395
00:23:15,590 --> 00:23:16,220
Zhou Jin,

396
00:23:17,200 --> 00:23:18,460
go report to Chief Tan.

397
00:23:19,090 --> 00:23:20,490
The leaders are waiting.

398
00:23:26,060 --> 00:23:26,780
Trust me.

399
00:23:29,050 --> 00:23:31,110
I'll report everything truthfully.

400
00:23:57,500 --> 00:23:58,830
There will be news soon.

401
00:24:02,260 --> 00:24:03,260
It's about time.

402
00:24:05,540 --> 00:24:06,470
Jiang Hansheng.

403
00:24:07,950 --> 00:24:09,470
I remember warning you before

404
00:24:09,470 --> 00:24:11,470
to keep your distance from Zhou Jin.

405
00:24:11,990 --> 00:24:14,320
Now it seems you didn't take it seriously.

406
00:24:15,190 --> 00:24:16,520
We're already married.

407
00:24:22,670 --> 00:24:23,260
Unlike you,

408
00:24:23,260 --> 00:24:24,340
someone who was born

409
00:24:24,340 --> 00:24:25,470
with a silver spoon,

410
00:24:26,020 --> 00:24:27,620
I haven't had much in my life.

411
00:24:27,870 --> 00:24:29,990
But the things
that originally belonged to me,

412
00:24:29,990 --> 00:24:31,790
I don't intend to give up easily.

413
00:24:37,910 --> 00:24:39,310
Until you clear your name

414
00:24:39,580 --> 00:24:41,110
and restore your identity,

415
00:24:41,990 --> 00:24:43,520
stop asking to see Zhou Jin.

416
00:24:43,590 --> 00:24:44,420
Why?

417
00:24:44,820 --> 00:24:45,470
Remember,

418
00:24:46,630 --> 00:24:48,340
the only reason
you're still standing here today

419
00:24:48,340 --> 00:24:49,940
and able to see Zhou Jin at all

420
00:24:50,100 --> 00:24:51,150
is because of me.

421
00:24:55,060 --> 00:24:55,990
What did you say?

422
00:24:57,100 --> 00:24:58,950
Don't use your undercover work

423
00:24:59,790 --> 00:25:01,450
to guilt-trip Zhou Jin again.

424
00:25:11,790 --> 00:25:12,910
-Professor Jiang.
-Professor Jiang.

425
00:25:12,910 --> 00:25:13,470
Professor Jiang!

426
00:25:13,470 --> 00:25:14,470
Professor Jiang!

427
00:25:25,230 --> 00:25:26,490
Qi Yan is Old Scorpion.

428
00:25:26,710 --> 00:25:27,640
All the cases

429
00:25:27,670 --> 00:25:29,000
have traced back to him.

430
00:25:29,230 --> 00:25:30,390
With Jiang Cheng's statement

431
00:25:30,390 --> 00:25:31,390
combined with what I've learned

432
00:25:31,390 --> 00:25:32,580
at Guhua Prison,

433
00:25:32,710 --> 00:25:35,310
this line of clues
can basically be connected.

434
00:25:36,540 --> 00:25:37,150
Tell me.

435
00:25:37,990 --> 00:25:39,260
After the 8/17 Case,

436
00:25:39,580 --> 00:25:40,820
the police found evidence

437
00:25:40,820 --> 00:25:41,990
at the scene indicating the presence

438
00:25:41,990 --> 00:25:43,230
of two suspects.

439
00:25:43,870 --> 00:25:45,500
After the task force was established,

440
00:25:45,500 --> 00:25:46,230
Leader Yao—

441
00:25:46,650 --> 00:25:48,870
with the help of the Provincial Bureau's
Crime Research Lab—

442
00:25:48,870 --> 00:25:49,950
quickly located

443
00:25:50,150 --> 00:25:52,300
some suspects hiding in the suburbs.

444
00:25:52,710 --> 00:25:54,030
There were four of them.

445
00:25:54,030 --> 00:25:54,730
It was confirmed

446
00:25:54,730 --> 00:25:55,400
that Qi Yan

447
00:25:55,670 --> 00:25:56,930
was the prime culprit.

448
00:25:57,620 --> 00:25:58,680
But the other three

449
00:25:58,730 --> 00:26:00,490
didn't match the forensic profile

450
00:26:00,490 --> 00:26:02,020
of the second suspect.

451
00:26:02,770 --> 00:26:03,630
In other words,

452
00:26:03,930 --> 00:26:05,480
one of the killers
involved in my brother's murder

453
00:26:05,480 --> 00:26:06,690
escaped.

454
00:26:07,340 --> 00:26:09,170
And his gun was never found.

455
00:26:09,690 --> 00:26:11,250
So to find more clues,

456
00:26:11,730 --> 00:26:13,250
the task force investigated

457
00:26:13,250 --> 00:26:15,010
the network of the four who were shot.

458
00:26:15,010 --> 00:26:16,620
They got a lead through a man

459
00:26:16,650 --> 00:26:17,650
named Feng He.

460
00:26:17,930 --> 00:26:18,860
They discovered

461
00:26:18,970 --> 00:26:19,730
that Feng He

462
00:26:20,020 --> 00:26:22,140
had very close dealings with He Wen.

463
00:26:22,930 --> 00:26:23,890
So I believe

464
00:26:24,650 --> 00:26:26,310
that after tracing this lead,

465
00:26:27,330 --> 00:26:28,730
Leader Yao secretly launched

466
00:26:28,730 --> 00:26:31,380
the undercover operation
codenamed "Cangfeng."

467
00:26:31,380 --> 00:26:33,620
He sent Jiang Cheng to Guhua Prison

468
00:26:33,650 --> 00:26:34,780
to get close to He Wen

469
00:26:34,930 --> 00:26:36,100
and gain his trust.

470
00:26:36,490 --> 00:26:37,970
Therefore, after Jiang Cheng was released,

471
00:26:37,970 --> 00:26:40,020
he caught He Wu's eye

472
00:26:40,250 --> 00:26:41,170
and successfully infiltrated

473
00:26:41,170 --> 00:26:42,570
the criminal syndicate.

474
00:26:44,380 --> 00:26:45,440
What you've told me

475
00:26:46,170 --> 00:26:48,450
is completely consistent with
what Leader Yao

476
00:26:48,450 --> 00:26:49,250
briefed me on.

477
00:26:49,620 --> 00:26:50,300
And

478
00:26:50,820 --> 00:26:52,100
you've filled in

479
00:26:53,380 --> 00:26:55,110
many of the gaps he left behind.

480
00:26:56,060 --> 00:26:56,820
So,

481
00:26:57,490 --> 00:26:59,950
you're also willing to
believe Jiang Cheng?

482
00:27:00,490 --> 00:27:01,890
I believe he is Cangfeng—

483
00:27:02,300 --> 00:27:02,860
but

484
00:27:03,100 --> 00:27:04,300
not because I want to.

485
00:27:05,380 --> 00:27:06,490
It's because the files

486
00:27:06,490 --> 00:27:07,620
have now been

487
00:27:07,860 --> 00:27:10,120
declassified, clearly and completely.

488
00:27:17,900 --> 00:27:19,390
[Jiang Cheng] [Deputy Captain of
the Criminal Investigation Brigade 2,]

489
00:27:18,380 --> 00:27:20,300
The classification level for Cangfeng
was extremely high.

490
00:27:19,390 --> 00:27:20,890
[Fengzhou District,
Haizhou City, Binjiang Province.]

491
00:27:20,690 --> 00:27:22,620
Unless they were killed, exposed,

492
00:27:22,620 --> 00:27:23,300
or

493
00:27:23,660 --> 00:27:25,190
[Codename: Cangfeng 1]

494
00:27:23,860 --> 00:27:25,190
returned successfully,

495
00:27:25,190 --> 00:27:27,590
[Person in charge: Yao Weihai,
Head of the 8/17 Task Force]

496
00:27:25,380 --> 00:27:27,580
the files would never be declassified.

497
00:27:27,750 --> 00:27:30,510
[Conditions for declassification: Death,
total exposure, or successful return.]

498
00:27:27,890 --> 00:27:28,540
That's why

499
00:27:28,540 --> 00:27:30,540
we couldn't find the files earlier.

500
00:27:30,580 --> 00:27:32,020
It was the same for Meng Junfeng

501
00:27:32,020 --> 00:27:32,690
and

502
00:27:33,210 --> 00:27:34,140
for Jiang Cheng.

503
00:27:34,890 --> 00:27:36,950
Actually, both of them are Cangfeng—

504
00:27:38,170 --> 00:27:39,500
covering for each other

505
00:27:39,780 --> 00:27:41,110
and serving as backups.

506
00:27:41,140 --> 00:27:41,940
It was

507
00:27:42,820 --> 00:27:43,970
a double safeguard.

508
00:27:45,930 --> 00:27:47,060
If that's the case,

509
00:27:47,690 --> 00:27:49,080
does that mean Jiang Cheng's position

510
00:27:49,080 --> 00:27:50,620
as Deputy Captain will be restored soon?

511
00:27:50,620 --> 00:27:51,620
But don't forget—

512
00:27:52,860 --> 00:27:54,140
how do you explain

513
00:27:55,580 --> 00:27:57,180
the fingerprints on the gun?

514
00:28:00,820 --> 00:28:01,620
But earlier,

515
00:28:02,060 --> 00:28:04,140
after Jiang Cheng knew the camera was off,

516
00:28:04,140 --> 00:28:06,620
the first thing he asked me was
who the mole was.

517
00:28:06,620 --> 00:28:08,420
He was very agitated at the time.

518
00:28:08,740 --> 00:28:11,330
He said it was the mole
who got Leader Yao killed.

519
00:28:11,330 --> 00:28:12,290
I could see

520
00:28:13,140 --> 00:28:14,940
that his feelings for Leader Yao

521
00:28:15,100 --> 00:28:16,060
ran very deep.

522
00:28:47,210 --> 00:28:48,410
Finished reporting?

523
00:28:50,380 --> 00:28:51,910
It took more than two hours.

524
00:28:54,410 --> 00:28:56,070
Why haven't you gone back yet?

525
00:29:05,140 --> 00:29:05,870
Much better.

526
00:29:06,930 --> 00:29:08,460
Did you take your medicine?

527
00:29:08,930 --> 00:29:10,460
I'll take it when I get home.

528
00:29:11,580 --> 00:29:12,640
I'll take you back.

529
00:29:21,210 --> 00:29:21,820
Zhou Jin.

530
00:29:27,820 --> 00:29:28,880
Are you exhausted?

531
00:29:35,490 --> 00:29:36,210
No.

532
00:29:37,970 --> 00:29:39,030
I'm full of energy.

533
00:29:40,490 --> 00:29:41,100
Let's go.

534
00:30:19,490 --> 00:30:20,220
Come with me.

535
00:31:07,860 --> 00:31:08,590
Does it hurt?

536
00:31:14,580 --> 00:31:15,170
Yes.

537
00:31:17,610 --> 00:31:18,940
It's been a long time...

538
00:31:21,490 --> 00:31:23,020
since I felt this much pain.

539
00:31:31,820 --> 00:31:32,550
Hansheng...

540
00:31:37,420 --> 00:31:38,550
I'm so tired.

541
00:31:40,060 --> 00:31:40,730
I want...

542
00:31:43,580 --> 00:31:45,620
I want to find a place to hide.

543
00:31:51,990 --> 00:31:52,790
I understand.

544
00:31:55,170 --> 00:31:56,830
But none of this is your fault.

545
00:31:58,930 --> 00:32:00,340
It's all my fault.

546
00:32:04,930 --> 00:32:06,820
On August 17,

547
00:32:08,340 --> 00:32:10,940
my brother wasn't supposed to
take that shift.

548
00:32:12,820 --> 00:32:15,080
He switched with someone just so he could

549
00:32:16,300 --> 00:32:17,690
celebrate my birthday.

550
00:32:21,170 --> 00:32:23,570
When they notified us
to identify the body,

551
00:32:24,970 --> 00:32:27,630
I couldn't even bring myself to
go in and see him.

552
00:32:30,040 --> 00:32:30,850
I hid.

553
00:32:34,450 --> 00:32:37,100
But actually, my heart hurt so much.

554
00:32:39,730 --> 00:32:41,930
I was very depressed during those days.

555
00:32:43,540 --> 00:32:45,340
Jiang Cheng kept smoking

556
00:32:46,380 --> 00:32:47,340
one cigarette

557
00:32:48,300 --> 00:32:50,380
after another in front of me.

558
00:32:51,340 --> 00:32:53,540
We argued endlessly

559
00:32:54,380 --> 00:32:55,890
over the most trivial,

560
00:32:56,860 --> 00:32:58,490
petty things.

561
00:33:02,010 --> 00:33:02,970
I thought...

562
00:33:05,300 --> 00:33:07,250
my life would never be happy again.

563
00:33:09,970 --> 00:33:10,780
I changed.

564
00:33:12,300 --> 00:33:13,450
I stopped crying

565
00:33:14,890 --> 00:33:17,020
and stopped letting myself feel pain.

566
00:33:18,690 --> 00:33:20,480
I thought he'd changed too—

567
00:33:22,300 --> 00:33:23,900
that he had become a bastard.

568
00:33:28,580 --> 00:33:30,060
But I was wrong.

569
00:33:36,540 --> 00:33:37,860
He never changed.

570
00:33:48,930 --> 00:33:50,930
He's been lying to me for five years.

571
00:33:54,380 --> 00:33:56,860
And I actually believed it for five years.

572
00:34:00,820 --> 00:34:02,950
I actually believed it for five years.

573
00:34:10,780 --> 00:34:11,550
Hansheng.

574
00:34:14,170 --> 00:34:15,650
Did I fail him?

575
00:34:18,620 --> 00:34:19,989
Was I wrong?

576
00:34:22,730 --> 00:34:23,980
I feel so guilty.

577
00:34:27,170 --> 00:34:28,460
I feel like...

578
00:34:30,650 --> 00:34:32,370
I've failed everyone.

579
00:34:35,540 --> 00:34:36,810
I've failed...

580
00:34:43,370 --> 00:34:44,620
What should I do?

581
00:35:05,190 --> 00:35:05,840
Zhou Jin.

582
00:35:07,660 --> 00:35:08,490
You're tired.

583
00:35:11,180 --> 00:35:11,910
Sleep.

584
00:35:15,260 --> 00:35:16,320
I'll stay with you.

585
00:35:50,470 --> 00:35:51,050
Thank you, sir.

586
00:35:51,050 --> 00:35:51,650
Okay.

587
00:35:51,720 --> 00:35:52,630
You're welcome.

588
00:35:52,630 --> 00:35:53,630
Here, Jin.

589
00:35:54,030 --> 00:35:55,050
Thanks, Jiang Cheng.

590
00:35:55,050 --> 00:35:56,420
Where did you get the money for soda?

591
00:35:56,420 --> 00:35:57,340
Guess.

592
00:35:58,120 --> 00:36:00,120
How much allowance do you get a week?

593
00:36:01,700 --> 00:36:02,970
We're keeping secrets
from each other now, huh?

594
00:36:02,970 --> 00:36:05,170
Wait for me! Why are you walking so fast?

595
00:37:00,670 --> 00:37:01,270
Zhou Jin.

596
00:37:04,960 --> 00:37:05,960
What should I do?

597
00:37:32,370 --> 00:37:33,370
Professor Jiang.

598
00:37:34,170 --> 00:37:35,900
You're not asleep yet, are you?

599
00:37:36,610 --> 00:37:37,400
There's something

600
00:37:37,400 --> 00:37:39,000
I'd like to discuss with you.

601
00:37:50,290 --> 00:37:50,890
Chief Tan.

602
00:37:51,390 --> 00:37:51,990
Chief Tan.

603
00:37:52,890 --> 00:37:54,820
Jiang Cheng has disclosed that...

604
00:37:55,570 --> 00:37:56,600
evidence of Hengyun Logistics Company

605
00:37:56,600 --> 00:37:58,420
engaging in illegal transactions,

606
00:37:58,420 --> 00:38:00,890
along with the contact list
of He Wu's company,

607
00:38:00,890 --> 00:38:02,280
has been copied onto some USB drives.

608
00:38:02,280 --> 00:38:04,510
The USB drive is
currently in the Hongtian Building.

609
00:38:04,510 --> 00:38:05,640
Whether it's true or not,

610
00:38:05,640 --> 00:38:06,700
go and retrieve it.

611
00:38:07,620 --> 00:38:08,050
Yes.

612
00:38:10,250 --> 00:38:12,260
The USB drive is
in a locker on the 7th floor.

613
00:38:12,260 --> 00:38:13,320
When you get there,

614
00:38:13,410 --> 00:38:14,490
go to the front desk first

615
00:38:14,490 --> 00:38:15,820
and ask for the spare key.

616
00:38:15,820 --> 00:38:16,880
Don't get it wrong.

617
00:38:17,450 --> 00:38:18,980
Third column from the left,

618
00:38:19,100 --> 00:38:19,820
fifth row.

619
00:38:21,580 --> 00:38:23,000
It's best to go after work hours.

620
00:38:23,000 --> 00:38:23,860
Around 9:30 PM.

621
00:38:24,170 --> 00:38:25,970
There won't be many people then.

622
00:39:07,690 --> 00:39:08,260
Freeze!

623
00:39:08,640 --> 00:39:09,660
Put the knife down.

624
00:39:09,660 --> 00:39:10,410
Hands up.

625
00:39:13,700 --> 00:39:15,530
-Freeze!
-Freeze!

626
00:39:17,130 --> 00:39:17,650
Freeze!

627
00:39:17,670 --> 00:39:18,330
Don't move!

628
00:39:19,510 --> 00:39:20,480
Don't come closer!

629
00:39:20,480 --> 00:39:21,730
You stay back too!

630
00:39:21,820 --> 00:39:22,570
Zhao Ping!

631
00:39:56,060 --> 00:39:56,780
Senior.

632
00:39:58,380 --> 00:39:59,150
You set me up.

633
00:40:08,600 --> 00:40:09,660
Why did you do this?

634
00:40:12,120 --> 00:40:13,720
You're not surprised at all.

635
00:40:14,370 --> 00:40:16,230
So you knew all along, didn't you?

636
00:40:16,700 --> 00:40:17,630
Come back with me

637
00:40:18,090 --> 00:40:19,250
and confess everything.

638
00:40:19,250 --> 00:40:20,310
Can I still go back,

639
00:40:21,230 --> 00:40:21,790
Senior?

640
00:40:21,840 --> 00:40:23,170
Don't call me "Senior"!

641
00:40:24,050 --> 00:40:27,010
Have you completely forgotten
the Police Academy's motto?

642
00:40:27,010 --> 00:40:28,740
The very first line is loyalty.

643
00:40:34,700 --> 00:40:35,620
I call you that

644
00:40:36,570 --> 00:40:38,900
because you said you like Armed Reaction.

645
00:40:38,920 --> 00:40:41,650
What does that have to do
with the Police Academy?

646
00:40:41,960 --> 00:40:42,560
Zhou Jin,

647
00:40:43,300 --> 00:40:44,630
I'm much older than you.

648
00:40:45,370 --> 00:40:47,900
I've let you ride
that privilege for too long.

649
00:40:48,290 --> 00:40:49,690
I'll say it one last time—

650
00:40:51,180 --> 00:40:52,180
come back with me.

651
00:40:52,210 --> 00:40:53,410
Don't pull that on me!

652
00:40:54,170 --> 00:40:55,980
Go ahead—give me three warnings,

653
00:40:55,980 --> 00:40:57,980
then shoot me for resisting arrest!

654
00:40:58,070 --> 00:40:58,670
Zhao Ping!

655
00:41:00,660 --> 00:41:01,790
Don't act like that!

656
00:41:02,740 --> 00:41:03,490
Come out.

657
00:41:04,260 --> 00:41:05,610
We'll talk when we get back.

658
00:41:05,610 --> 00:41:07,170
What are you guys doing?

659
00:41:07,940 --> 00:41:10,740
Stop looking at me
like you're heartbroken, okay?

660
00:41:10,990 --> 00:41:12,550
You are cops,

661
00:41:12,930 --> 00:41:14,370
and I'm a criminal!

662
00:41:15,170 --> 00:41:16,830
Why do you want to take me back?

663
00:41:17,300 --> 00:41:18,360
To interrogate me?

664
00:41:18,450 --> 00:41:20,580
To ask if I have some tragic backstory?

665
00:41:29,840 --> 00:41:31,160
Don't come closer!

666
00:41:37,840 --> 00:41:39,200
Why did you do this?

667
00:41:39,270 --> 00:41:40,230
For money!

668
00:41:45,780 --> 00:41:47,780
If I had gotten that USB drive today,

669
00:41:48,530 --> 00:41:49,780
one million would have been wired

670
00:41:49,780 --> 00:41:50,990
into my overseas account!

671
00:41:50,990 --> 00:41:52,650
How could I refuse that money?

672
00:41:53,090 --> 00:41:54,450
I'm not like you guys!

673
00:41:55,700 --> 00:41:57,360
All that so-called fairness,

674
00:41:57,890 --> 00:41:59,520
justice, and faith

675
00:41:59,860 --> 00:42:01,450
have nothing to do with me!

676
00:42:01,450 --> 00:42:02,420
You're not that kind of person!

677
00:42:02,420 --> 00:42:03,900
I am!

678
00:42:03,970 --> 00:42:05,330
This is the kind of person I am!

679
00:42:05,330 --> 00:42:06,390
I don't believe it!

680
00:42:07,270 --> 00:42:09,400
All these years,
you worked so hard on cases.

681
00:42:09,400 --> 00:42:10,860
Was all of that just an act?

682
00:42:15,050 --> 00:42:17,510
Zhou Jin, don't put
that kind of weight on me.

683
00:42:18,010 --> 00:42:20,470
I know you can't accept
what happened today.

684
00:42:20,800 --> 00:42:21,800
Idealism—

685
00:42:22,400 --> 00:42:23,730
who wouldn't want that?

686
00:42:24,130 --> 00:42:26,220
But fate isn't fair.

687
00:42:27,000 --> 00:42:29,610
It never laid out a straight road for me!

688
00:42:31,050 --> 00:42:33,580
You should understand that,
right, Zhou Jin?

689
00:42:34,370 --> 00:42:35,210
Sometimes,

690
00:42:35,780 --> 00:42:37,300
one bolt from the blue

691
00:42:38,700 --> 00:42:41,100
is enough to
change a person's entire life.

692
00:42:42,970 --> 00:42:43,900
Then tell me...

693
00:42:46,940 --> 00:42:48,220
what was

694
00:42:48,220 --> 00:42:49,680
that one bolt from the blue

695
00:42:50,180 --> 00:42:51,510
that changed your life?

696
00:42:56,860 --> 00:42:58,090
The same one as yours.

697
00:42:59,450 --> 00:43:00,250
The 8/17 Case.

698
00:43:02,260 --> 00:43:03,010
That day...

699
00:43:04,420 --> 00:43:05,090
I was there too.
